Are your tensors one and two scalars?
In that case, the error would make sense, as sparse tensor indices have rank 2 (The shape is [N, ndims], where N is the number of non-zero elements and ndims the rank of the underlying tensor).

body:
Are your tensors `one` and `two` scalars?
In that case, the error would make sense, as sparse tensor indices have rank 2 (The shape is `[N, ndims]`, where `N` is the number of non-zero elements and `ndims` the rank of the underlying tensor).
